BFN 

  [Text] According to the Ministry of Agriculture and Food 
Industry, provinces in northern region have completed their 
harvest on over one million hectares of fifth-month spring rice. 
Except for the provinces of Thua Thien-Hue and Quang Tri which 
have suffered from a bad harvest of about 12-13 tonnes per 
hectare and a gross collection of 80,000 tonnes of grain, Ha 
Tinh and Nghe An have reaped an increase of 40,000 tonnes. All 
other provinces enjoy larger or equal harvests in comparison 
with last spring rice planting season. 
  According to local agriculture offices, the total grain 
output of northern provinces this year is about 4.220 million 
tonnes, or nearly the same as last year's spring rice season of 
4.223 million tonnes. 
  Provinces in northern region also produced about 1.2 million 
tonnes of other crops, thus bringing the total agricultural 
output of +another good harvest this year to 5.4 million tonnes. 

